<P>DISPOSITION&mdash;THIS MOTION FOR LEAVE TO APPEAL</P>
<P>THE DECISION OF Wilson, J.</P>
<P>DATED April 4, 2018 IS</P>
<P>Leave to appeal is granted with respect to the issue of whether the Master had jurisdiction to bifurcate the issues of liability and damages. We agree with Wilson J.'s observation that clarification is required on this issue from an appellate authority. We dismiss the motion for leave with respect to the issue of whether, if jurisdiction did exist bifurcation should have been ordered. Costs of this motion are reserved to the panel hearing the appeal.</P>
